---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RelatedWorkflows from '../../components/RelatedWorkflows.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Workflows', url: '/workflows' },
  { name: 'Marketplace', url: '/workflows/marketplace' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How is this different from other breeder listings?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ Marketplace is connected to actual breeding program data. Health testing results and program details on a profile are the breeder’s own attestation, backed by the records they maintain on the platform; BreederHQ does not vouch for them. Profile Indicators (response time, completed transactions) reflect platform account history.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does identity and credential display work?',
    answer: 'Badges indicate verified achievements like "Health Tested Program," "Pedigree Documented," or "Established Breeder." They\'re earned automatically when your records meet the criteria, so there is no manual application needed.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What kinds of listings can I create?',
    answer: 'Three types: individual animal listings (animals available for sale or adoption), offspring group listings (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or service listings (stud services, guardian homes, trained animals, rehoming, co-ownership). You choose which types to use.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I have to list all my animals?',
    answer: 'No. You control exactly which animals are visible on the marketplace. Keep your program private or make it public, and you decide for each animal individually.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do inquiries work?',
    answer: 'Buyer inquiries come directly to your BreederHQ dashboard. You can respond, qualify leads, and manage all communications in one place alongside your other client management.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I find stud services or breeding partners for my own animals?',
    answer: 'Yes. The marketplace doubles as a cross-network search for breeders. Filter by species, breed, health test results, color genetics, COI, and location to find genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ community.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What does it cost to list?',
    answer: 'Animal listings are a one-time fee based on species, with no monthly charges and no commissions on sales. All listing fees are currently waived during our early access period.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is a Storefront and why does it matter?',
    answer: 'Your Storefront is your public, branded presence on the BreederHQ Marketplace. Logo, banner, bio, your active listings, and your Breeding Programs in one page at your own marketplace.breederhq.com URL. Buyers searching the marketplace find breeders with complete Storefronts first; empty profiles drop out of results. Setup takes about 15 minutes.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What does a Breeding Program do?',
    answer: 'A Breeding Program is the operational hub for one of your lines. It holds your animals, plans, offspring, listings, waitlist, inquiries, and announcements in one place, and lets you set rules that automate listing offspring at weaning, applying default prices by sex, opening and closing waitlists, gating "Coming Soon" listings, and enforcing minimum photo counts. Announcements push to your public Storefront and to every committed buyer\'s client portal in one shot.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I show my BreederHQ programs and listings on my own website?',
    answer: 'Yes. The Embed Widget gives you one HTML snippet that you paste onto any page of your own site (Wix, Squarespace, WordPress, Webflow, Shopify, custom HTML). Your site then shows your live BreederHQ data and updates automatically every time something changes in BreederHQ. You choose what to show (full Storefront or a single program), which sections appear (Programs, Litters, Available Offspring, Individual Animals), and the theme.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need a Breeding Program to use the Marketplace?',
    answer: 'No, but you should have one. You can post individual animal listings without a program. With a program, your listings, waitlist, announcements, and inquiries all live in one operational hub, and the rules engine handles repetitive work (auto-listing weaned offspring, default pricing, waitlist scoping) for you.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Breeder Marketplace, Storefront, Programs, and Embed Widget | BreederHQ"
  description="Get discovered by serious buyers with a complete Storefront, automate your sales pipeline with Breeding Programs, and show your live listings on your own Wix, Squarespace, or WordPress site with the Embed Widget. Profile Indicators based on platform account history."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Workflows</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Marketplace</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Section 1: What This Page Is About -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Get Discovered by Serious Buyers</h1>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The BreederHQ Marketplace connects responsible breeders with educated buyers. List individual animals, offspring groups (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or stud service offerings. Health testing records are the breeder’s own attestation, surfaced from data they maintain on the platform. You can search the entire BreederHQ network for genetically compatible matches. Your reputation is visible, verifiable, and valuable.
        </p>
      </aside>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Quality breeders can struggle to stand out online. Volume operations dominate search results. Undocumented breeders undercut prices. Serious buyers can't easily tell the difference. The BreederHQ Marketplace changes that by putting your real program data front and center.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Breeders Search for This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Why finding the right buyers is hard</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Good breeders face constant challenges:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Generic listing sites treat responsible breeders the same as puppy mills</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Your health testing investment doesn't translate to visibility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Buyers can't verify claims, so they don't trust anyone</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Price shoppers waste your time with inquiries they'll never follow through</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Your website doesn't rank against sites with bigger marketing budgets</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Word of mouth is slow and unpredictable</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Doing the right thing should give you a competitive advantage. Usually it doesn't.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: How Breeders Usually Handle It -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">How breeders try to get discovered</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Personal websites</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You build a website, write about your program, post photos. But SEO is competitive. Your site ranks page 10 while questionable breeders dominate page 1.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Generic listing sites</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Sites like PuppyFind, NextDayPets, DreamHorse, EquineNow, breed-specific classifieds, and Craigslist. Anyone can list with no identity confirmation or registry passthrough, so your documented program sits right next to volume ads.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Social media</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Facebook groups, Instagram. Good for community, but algorithms limit reach. Building an audience takes years of consistent content.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Breed club referrals</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Registry referral lists. Trusted but limited reach. Most buyers don't know to look there.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Word of mouth</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Happy clients refer friends. The best leads, but you can't control the volume or timing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Where That Breaks Down -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Where those approaches stretch thin</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">No easy way to prove quality</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Every listing claims "health tested" and "raised with love." Buyers have no quick way to verify any of it, so they end up skeptical of everyone, including you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Documented programs look the same as the rest</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            On generic listing sites, a responsible breeder's ad looks identical to a volume operation's. Sometimes worse, because volume operations invest heavily in professional photos and copy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Price becomes the default differentiator</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            When buyers can't evaluate quality at a glance, they shop on price. Your fully health-tested, documented animal loses to a cheaper "no papers" listing every time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Unqualified inquiries eat your time</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Inquiries from people who want an animal tomorrow, don't want to fill out an application, or can't afford your pricing add up fast. Hours spent on leads that were never going to convert.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Reputation isn't portable</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Your Facebook reviews don't show up on your website. Your OFA, PennHIP, or genetic panel results aren't visible on listing sites. Your reputation is scattered across platforms and hard to verify.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Marketing takes time you don't have</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You're busy with actual breeding work. Social media management, SEO, content creation: full-time jobs on top of the full-time job you already have.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: What a Correct System Looks Like -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">What it looks like when your records are connected to your listings</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Verify claims with real data</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Health testing badges backed by actual test records</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Pedigree records grounded in your documented lineage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Program history visible (years breeding, litters produced)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Buyers see proof, not promises</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Surface quality programs</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Breeders with attested and registry-confirmed health testing rank higher</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Documented programs get more visibility</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Investment in quality translates to marketplace advantage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>No pay-to-play advertising that lets anyone buy the top spot</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Attract educated buyers</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Buyers who understand why health testing matters</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>People willing to wait for the right match</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Families who value transparency and documentation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Fewer tire-kickers, more serious inquiries</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Cross-network matching for breeders</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Search for genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ network</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Filter by species, breed, health results, color genetics, COI, and location</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Discover stud services, program offerings, and co-ownership opportunities</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Reach out directly through the same inquiry system your own buyers use</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Integrated inquiry management</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Inquiries flow directly into your management system</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Qualify, respond, and track leads in one place</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>No separate inbox to check</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Communication history preserved</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Control over visibility</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Choose which animals to list</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Set your program's public profile</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Hide or show based on availability</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Your data, your decisions</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: How BreederHQ Supports This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">BreederHQ Marketplace rewards responsible breeding</h2>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Your health testing records become public attestations on your profile. Your documented pedigrees prove lineage. Your program history shows experience. Buyers see real data, not marketing claims. Quality breeders finally get the visibility they deserve.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Inquiries arrive in your dashboard alongside your other client management. One system for breeding records, client relationships, and marketplace presence.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="https://accounts.breederhq.com/register?intent=breeder_dashboard" class="inline-block bg-white text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          Get Started Free
        </a>
        <a href="/workflows/waitlists-and-placement" class="inline-block bg-transparent border-2 border-white text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          See waitlist management →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6.5: Storefront, Programs, and Embed Widget -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Your Storefront, Your Programs, Your Website</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        Listings are only one piece of marketplace presence. The breeders who get found, get trusted, and get serious inquiries are the ones who set up three things: a complete Storefront, at least one active Breeding Program, and (if they run their own website) the Embed Widget. Each one takes about 15 minutes. Together they decide whether buyers see a real business or an empty profile.
      </p>

      <figure class="my-12">
        <img
          src="/images/screenshots/breeder_storefront.png"
          alt="Example BreederHQ Storefront with logo, banner, bio, breeding programs, and active animal listings on a single branded page"
          class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-xl border border-gray-200"
          loading="lazy"
          width="1600"
          height="1000"
        />
        <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center mt-3 italic">
          A complete Storefront: logo, banner, bio, programs, and active listings on one branded page at your own marketplace URL.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <!-- Storefront -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Your Storefront Is Your Shopfront</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Buyers searching the BreederHQ Marketplace right now are filtering by species, breed, and program style. The breeders they find first are the ones with a complete Storefront. The breeders they trust are the ones whose pages look like a real business. If your Storefront is empty or default, you are effectively invisible to those buyers, no matter how many listings you post.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What a complete Storefront actually does:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Buyers can find you.</strong> Marketplace search and discovery favor breeders with complete Storefronts. An empty profile drops out of results.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>You look like a real business.</strong> Logo, banner, bio. Three fields. They make the difference between "this is a hobby" and "this is a serious operation."</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Every listing performs better.</strong> Boosts, featured slots, and inquiries all funnel through your Storefront. A complete page raises the ceiling on every listing you post.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>One branded URL.</strong> Your Storefront lives at your own marketplace.breederhq.com slug. Bookmarkable, shareable, and consistent everywhere you point people.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Breeding Programs -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Breeding Programs Run Your Sales While You Sleep</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          A Breeding Program is the operational hub for one of your lines. It holds your animals, your plans, your offspring, your listings, your waitlist, your inquiries, and your announcements in one place. More importantly, it lets you set rules that automate the work you used to do by hand every night.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What a Breeding Program automates:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Listings post themselves.</strong> Set a rule: when an offspring hits weaning age and meets your minimum photo count, list it. Default prices apply by sex automatically.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Waitlists run themselves.</strong> Open a waitlist when a plan is announced. Close it when it fills. Scope by program, by breeder, or both. All by rule, all without you in the loop.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>"Coming Soon" gating.</strong> Offspring stay in a soft-launch state until you flip them live, so buyers see momentum before the listing opens.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Announcements reach everyone in one shot.</strong> Post once from the Announcements tab. It pushes to your public Storefront, to your client portal, and to the followers feed of every committed buyer. One post, three places.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Sales Pipeline view.</strong> Track every prospect from first inquiry through approval, across all your programs, in one dashboard.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Multi-breed support.</strong> Run several closely related lines under one operation without duplicating data.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Embed Widget -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Already Have Your Own Website? Stop Updating It By Hand</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          If you run a Wix, Squarespace, WordPress, Webflow, Shopify, or custom site, your "Available" page is almost certainly out of date right now. The Embed Widget fixes that for good. Copy one snippet from BreederHQ. Paste it onto your site. From that moment on, every change you make in BreederHQ shows up on your own website automatically. You never edit that page again.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">What the Embed Widget does on your site:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>One paste, then forget about it.</strong> A single HTML snippet works on any platform that lets you paste HTML. No plugin, no framework, no maintenance.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Pick what to show.</strong> Your full Storefront on one page, or a single program on a dedicated subpage. Toggle on Programs, Litters, Available Offspring, or Individual Animals in any combination.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Live data, your domain.</strong> Sell an offspring in BreederHQ, and the same minute your website updates. Open a waitlist, and it appears. Buyers landing on your site see what is actually available right now.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
            <span><strong>Match your site's design.</strong> Light, dark, or branded theme. Width control. The widget visually fits the page you drop it on.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span class="mr-3">•</span>
