  <!-- Section 9: FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 faq-section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Frequently asked questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How is this different from other breeder listings?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>BreederHQ Marketplace is connected to actual breeding program data. Health testing results and program details on a profile are the breeder’s own attestation, backed by the records they maintain on the platform. BreederHQ does not vouch for them; Profile Indicators reflect platform account history.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How does identity and credential display work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Profile Indicators reflect your account history on the platform: typical response time, completed transactions, open disputes. Where a public registry confirms a credential (e.g. OFA), a registry-passthrough indicator may also appear. BreederHQ does not vouch for credentials beyond what these passthroughs return.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What kinds of listings can I create?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Three types: individual animal listings (animals available for sale or adoption), offspring group listings (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or service listings (stud services, guardian homes, trained animals, rehoming, co-ownership). You choose which types to use.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Do I have to list all my animals?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>No. You control exactly which animals are visible on the marketplace. Keep your program private or make it public, and you decide for each animal individually.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How do inquiries work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Buyer inquiries come directly to your BreederHQ dashboard. You can respond, qualify leads, and manage all communications in one place alongside your other client management.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I find stud services or breeding partners for my own animals?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The marketplace doubles as a cross-network search for breeders. Filter by species, breed, health test results, color genetics, COI, and location to find genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ community.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What does it cost to list?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Animal listings are a one-time fee based on species, with no monthly charges and no commissions on sales. All listing fees are currently waived during our early access period.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What is a Storefront and why does it matter?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Your Storefront is your public, branded presence on the BreederHQ Marketplace. Logo, banner, bio, your active listings, and your Breeding Programs in one page at your own marketplace.breederhq.com URL. Buyers searching the marketplace find breeders with complete Storefronts first; empty profiles drop out of results. Setup takes about 15 minutes.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What does a Breeding Program do?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>A Breeding Program is the operational hub for one of your lines. It holds your animals, plans, offspring, listings, waitlist, inquiries, and announcements in one place, and lets you set rules that automate listing offspring at weaning, applying default prices by sex, opening and closing waitlists, gating "Coming Soon" listings, and enforcing minimum photo counts. Announcements push to your public Storefront and to every committed buyer's client portal in one shot.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I show my BreederHQ programs and listings on my own website?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The Embed Widget gives you one HTML snippet that you paste onto any page of your own site (Wix, Squarespace, WordPress, Webflow, Shopify, custom HTML). Your site then shows your live BreederHQ data and updates automatically every time something changes in BreederHQ. You choose what to show (full Storefront or a single program), which sections appear (Programs, Litters, Available Offspring, Individual Animals), and the theme.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Do I need a Breeding Program to use the Marketplace?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>No, but you should have one. You can post individual animal listings without a program. With a program, your listings, waitlist, announcements, and inquiries all live in one operational hub, and the rules engine handles repetitive work (auto-listing weaned offspring, default pricing, waitlist scoping) for you.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

